title: Claude Monet Irises Paint Tube Pen
description:
Paint tube pen developed from Claude Monet’s Irises, 1914-17, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

It may look like a tube of paint, but when the top is taken off it reveals a pen tip.  Comfortable grip for writing.  Has a small image of Claude Monet’s Irises, 1914-17, on the tube’s wrap.

  • Dimensions:  4.33 x 1.25 x .86 in.
  • Ink Color:  Black Ink
